== Salsa Fresca ==

Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and finely dice @red onion{1}. Pat
@chicken breast strips{10%ounces} dry with #paper towels{}.

Set aside 2 TBSP onion (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Heat a large drizzle of
@vegetable oil{3%teaspoons} in a large, preferably nonstick, #pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add chicken, remaining onion, @blackening spice{1%tablespoon},
@salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is browned
and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a large #bowl{}.
Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, zest and quarter @lime{1}. Finely dice @Roma tomato{1}. In a medium
bowl, combine tomato and 1 TBSP reserved onion (3 TBSP for 4 servings); add more
onion to taste. Squeeze in juice from 1 lime wedge (2 lime wedges for 4) and
season with salt and pepper.

== Lime Crema ==

In a small bowl, combine @sour cream{2%tablespoons}, lime zest (to taste), and
juice from 1 lime wedge (2 lime wedges for 4 servings). Add water, 1 tsp at a
time, until mixture reaches drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

== Quesadillas ==

Place @flour tortilla{2} on a work surface. Evenly sprinkle @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}
and @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup} onto one side of each tortilla. Top cheese
with filling, then fold tortillas in half to create quesadillas.

Heat a drizzle of oil and @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in pan
used for chicken over medium-high heat. Working in batches, add quesadillas and
cook until golden brown on the first side, ~{1-2%minutes}. Flip and cook
~{1%minute} more. Transfer to a paper-towel-lined #plate{}.

Transfer quesadillas to a #cutting board{}; slice into thirds and divide between
plates. Serve with salsa, lime crema, and @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} (to taste).
Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.